data.chText: （人或动物的）气质，性情，性格，禀性
data.enText: a person's or an animal's nature as shown in the way they behave or react to situations or people
a horse with an excellent temperament

data.chText: 她生性异想天开，浪漫多情。
data.enText: She's a dreamer and a romantic by temperament .

data.chText: 易冲动；（性情）暴躁；喜怒无常
data.enText: the tendency to get emotional and excited very easily and behave in an unreasonable way
an actor given to displays of temperament

simple_means.memory_skill: tempera〔= temper〕时间引起的现象 + ment 结果 → 长时间养成的〔脾气〕→ 性情

tr: an adjustment of the intervals (as in tuning a keyboard instrument) so that the scale can be used to play in different keys
excessive emotionalism or irritability and excitability (especially when displayed openly)

value.def: Your temperament is your basic nature, especially as it is shown in the way that you react to situations or to other people.

example.ex: His impulsive temperament regularly got him into difficulties...
example.tran: 他容易冲动，经常因此惹麻烦。

example.ex: She was furtive and vicious by temperament.
example.tran: 她本来做事就偷偷摸摸，心肠狠毒。

value.def: Temperament is the tendency to behave in an uncontrolled, bad-tempered, or unreasonable way.

example.ex: Mark does have a habit of allowing his temperament to get the better of him...
example.tran: 马克的确经常由着自己的性子来。

example.ex: Some of the models were given to fits of temperament.

value.tran: 爱发脾气;脾气乖张;喜怒无常
